WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.539
Welcome to First Aid Angel. In any emergency,
00:00:02.539 --> 00:00:05.077
remember the seven steps of DRSABCD — your
00:00:05.077 --> 00:00:07.616
action plan for saving a life.

00:00:08.016 --> 00:00:10.895
D is for Danger. Check the area for
00:00:10.895 --> 00:00:13.775
anything that could harm you, bystanders, or the
00:00:13.775 --> 00:00:16.654
casualty — traffic, fire, electricity, or water.

00:00:17.054 --> 00:00:19.949
R is for Response. Tap the shoulders and
00:00:19.949 --> 00:00:22.844
ask loudly: can you hear me? Squeeze the
00:00:22.844 --> 00:00:25.738
hand. If there is no response, act fast.

00:00:26.138 --> 00:00:28.646
S is for Send for help. Call emergency
00:00:28.646 --> 00:00:31.154
services on 995 immediately, or ask a bystander
00:00:31.154 --> 00:00:33.661
to call and report back to you.

00:00:34.061 --> 00:00:36.398
A is for Airway. Tilt the head back
00:00:36.398 --> 00:00:38.736
gently and lift the chin to open the
00:00:38.736 --> 00:00:41.073
airway. Clear any visible obstructions.

00:00:41.474 --> 00:00:44.044
B is for Breathing. Look, listen and feel
00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:46.613
for normal breathing for up to ten seconds.
00:00:46.613 --> 00:00:49.183
If absent or abnormal, begin CPR.

00:00:49.583 --> 00:00:51.835
C is for CPR. Give thirty chest compressions
00:00:51.835 --> 00:00:54.088
at one hundred to one hundred twenty per
00:00:54.088 --> 00:00:56.340
minute, followed by two rescue breaths. Continue until
00:00:56.340 --> 00:00:58.592
help arrives.

00:00:58.992 --> 00:01:01.140
D is for Defibrillation. Attach an AED as
00:01:01.140 --> 00:01:03.288
soon as one is available and follow the
00:01:03.288 --> 00:01:05.436
voice prompts. Continue CPR until the device tells
00:01:05.436 --> 00:01:07.583
you otherwise.

00:01:07.984 --> 00:01:10.151
You are now an Angel in someone's emergency.
00:01:10.151 --> 00:01:12.318
Learn more and find an AED near you
00:01:12.318 --> 00:01:14.486
at firstaidangel.org.
